title.rendered: Pakistan vs Ireland, Women’s T20 World Cup 2023: Fantasy Team, Probable Playing XIs, Pitch Report & Fantasy Tips

content.rendered:
We have opted for a fantasy cricket team based on the recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable Playing XIs for Pakistan & Ireland

Pakistan: Muneeba Ali (wk), Javeria Khan, Bismah Maroof (c), Nida Dar, Sidra Ameen, Ayesha Naseem, Aliya Riaz,  Fatima Sana, Aiman Anwer, Nashra Sandhu, Sadia Iqbal

Ireland: Amy Hunter, Gaby Lewis, Orla Prendergast, Laura Delany (c), Eimear Richardson, Louise Little, Mary Waldron (wk), Leah Paul, Arlene Kelly, Cara Murray, Jane Maguire

Pitch Report for Pakistan vs Ireland, Women’s T20 World Cup 2023

(Based on the last three games)

1st innings average score: 135

2nd innings average score: 142

Wickets per innings: 5

Type: Balanced

Wins

Batting 1st: 33%

Batting 2nd: 67%

Also Read:

New Zealand vs England, 1st Test, 2023: Fantasy Tips

Australia vs Bangladesh, Women’s T20 World Cup 2023: Fantasy Tips

UAE vs Afghanistan, 1st T20I, 2023: Fantasy Tips

Fantasy Tips of The Day

In the T20Is between these teams, Javeria Khan has slammed the most runs. She has collected 346 runs at an average of 49.

Meanwhile, Nida Dar tops the bowling chart: 18 wickets in 15 games. She also has impressive numbers with the bat against Ireland: 208 runs at 34.

Gaby Lewis likes smashing the Pakistan bowlers. In a mere five outings, she has fetched 193 runs at 48 including two fifties.

As many as three Pakistan players made it to the Best11 in four of the last five games: Nashra Sandhu, Ayesha Naseem, and Sadia Iqbal. To make matters interesting, Nashra has not gone wicketless for eight consecutive games.

Laura Delany provides points with both bat and ball. Above all, her 13 wickets are the most for Ireland against Pakistan.

Amy Hunter has the best fantasy numbers for an Ireland batter. In her last five competitive T20s, she has scored 108 runs at 22.

All four half-centuries registered at Newlands in the last three games have been by the top-order batters.
